de.boereck.matcher.helpers

Interface TypeCheck<I,O>

  • Type Parameters:
    I - type of objects that can be checked for it's type
    O - type the tested object can be assigned to.
    All Superinterfaces:
    AdvPredicate<I>, Predicate<I>
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface TypeCheck<I,O>
extends AdvPredicate<I>
    Function checking if an instance of I is either instance of or exactly of type O. It is essential for this interface, that if Predicate.test(Object) returns true, the tested object is assignable to type O.

    • Method Detail

      • andTest

        default TypeCheck<I,O> andTest(Predicate<O> otherTest)
                        throws NullPointerException
        This is a lazy concatenation of tests. The returned TypeCheck will first test this predicate and only if this returns true will test the given otherTest. The result will be the logical short-circuiting AND operation.

        Of any exceptions are thrown during evaluation of either predicate are passed on to the caller of the composed predicate. If this predicate throws an exception, the otherTest predicate will not be called.

        Parameters:
        otherTest - will be evaluated if this predicate evaluates to true and throws no exception. The result of the given otherTest predicate will be combined with logical AND with the result of this predicate. Since otherTest will only be evaluated if this predicate evaluates to true, the tested object will automatically casted to the tested type.
        Returns:
        a composed predicate, representing the lazily evaluate logical
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if predicate otherTest is null.
        See Also:
        for composition without casting of tested object. AND of this predicate and the {@code otherTest} predicate.

      • impliesTest

        default AdvPredicate<I> impliesTest(Predicate<? super O> otherTest)
                             throws NullPointerException
        This is a lazy concatenation of tests. The returned TypeCheck will first test this predicate and only if this returns true will test the given otherTest. The result will be the logical short-circuiting IMPLIES operation.

        Of any exceptions are thrown during evaluation of either predicate are passed on to the caller of the composed predicate. If this predicate throws an exception, the otherTest predicate will not be called.

        Parameters:
        otherTest - will be evaluated if this predicate evaluates to true and throws no exception. The result of the given otherTest predicate will be combined with logical IMPLIES with the result of this predicate. Since otherTest will only be evaluated if this predicate evaluates to true, the tested object will automatically casted to the tested type.
        Returns:
        a composed predicate, representing the lazily evaluate logical
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if predicate otherTest is null.
        See Also:
        for composition without casting of tested object. AND of this predicate and the {@code otherTest} predicate.

      • thenMap

        default <R> OptionalMapper<I,R> thenMap(Function<? super O,? extends R> f)
                                 throws NullPointerException
        Returns a function that performs a map operation after this type check, if this type check succeeds in the first place. If the type checks succeeds the returned Optional will hold the result of the call of mapping function f, otherwise the function will return an empty Optional.
        Type Parameters:
        R - target type of the mapping operation.
        Parameters:
        f - mapping function that will take the casted output of this TypeCheck and called with the result of the cast. The result of this mapping function will be returned in an Optional object from the function returned by this method.
        Returns:
        function that performs a map operation after this type check, if this type check succeeds in the first place.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if mapping function f is null.

      • thenFlatMap

        default <R> OptionalMapper<I,R> thenFlatMap(Function<? super O,Optional<R>> f)
                                     throws NullPointerException
        Returns a function that performs a map operation after this type check, if this type check succeeds in the first place. If the type checks succeeds the returned Optional will be the result of the call of mapping function f, otherwise the function will return an empty Optional.
        Type Parameters:
        R - target type of the mapping operation.
        Parameters:
        f - mapping function that will take the casted output of this TypeCheck and called with the result of the cast. The result of this mapping function will be returned as the result of the function returned by this method.
        Returns:
        function that performs a map operation after this type check, if this type check succeeds in the first place.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if mapping function f is null.
